{
  "texts": [
    "Additionally, we would like to point out that the summary level evaluation in Section 5.2 could benefit from a human evaluation study on the quality of the system and reference summaries.",
    "First, it has been pointed out in Goyal et al. (2022) that automatic metrics (e.g.",
    "ROUGE, BERTScore), though being commonly used, may not always correlate well with human evaluation.",
    "In this respect, we conducted the first manual, qualitative evaluation of the system summaries for the included entities (see Figures 2, 3, 4).",
    "Our analysis shows that adding predicted or gold salient entities to summarization models helps enhance summary quality by alleviating hallucinations in summaries."
  ]
}